 Bullseye ships openexr 2.5.4 which is outside the upstream affected
 version range. This patch documents non-applicability; no source
 changes are required.
Origin: vendor, Root.io
Author: Root.io Patch Team <security@root.io>
Last-Update: 2026-07-17

--- /dev/null
+++ b/ROOT-SECURITY-RELEASE-CVE-2026-34380.md
@@ -0,0 +1,101 @@
+# CVE-2026-34380 — Not Affected Analysis for OpenEXR 2.5.4 (Debian Bullseye)
+
+## Summary
+
+CVE-2026-34380 does **not** affect OpenEXR 2.5.4. The vulnerability is a
+signed-integer overflow in the OpenEXRCore C PXR24 decoder
+(`undo_pxr24_impl` in `src/lib/OpenEXRCore/internal_pxr24.c`), introduced
+with the 3.x C-core rewrite. Debian Bullseye ships the legacy IlmImf C++
+tree only; the vulnerable expression and file do not exist.
+
+---
+
+## CVE Description
+
+> OpenEXR provides the specification and reference implementation of the EXR
+> file format. From 3.2.0 to before 3.2.7, 3.3.9, and 3.4.9, a signed integer
+> overflow exists in `undo_pxr24_impl()` in
+> `src/lib/OpenEXRCore/internal_pxr24.c`. The expression `(uint64_t)(w * 3)`
+> computes `w * 3` as a signed 32-bit integer before casting to `uint64_t`.
+> When `w` is large, this wraparound can cause a bounds check to pass
+> incorrectly, allowing the decode loop to write beyond the allocated output
+> buffer. Fixed in 3.2.7, 3.3.9, and 3.4.9.
+
+**Affected range:** 3.2.0 ≤ version < 3.2.7; 3.3.0 ≤ version < 3.3.9; 3.4.0 ≤ version < 3.4.9
+**Fixed in:** 3.2.7 / 3.3.9 / 3.4.9
+**Debian Bullseye ships:** OpenEXR **2.5.4** (`2.5.4-2+deb11u1`)
+
+2.5.4 is below the affected lower bound of 3.2.0 by an entire major branch.
+
+---
+
+## Upstream Fix (for reference — not applicable here)
+
+Upstream commit `f5beec2bd8636102e74460a0b624d3e26efc546f` changes:
+
+```c
+/* before (vulnerable) */
+if (nDec + (uint64_t) (w * 3) > outSize)
+nDec += (uint64_t) (w * 3);
+lastIn += w * 4;
+
+/* after (fixed) */
+if (nDec + (uint64_t) w * 3 > outSize)
+nDec += (uint64_t) w * 3;
+lastIn += (uint64_t) w * 4;
+```
+
+That is, cast `w` to `uint64_t` **before** multiplying — not a width-reject
+guard.
+
+---
+
+## Why 2.5.4 Is Not Affected
+
+### 1. Vulnerable file / expression absent
+
+| Upstream fix target | Present in 2.5.4? |
+|---------------------|-------------------|
+| `src/lib/OpenEXRCore/internal_pxr24.c` | **No** |
+| `(uint64_t)(w * 3)` cast-after-multiply | **No** |
+| `undo_pxr24_impl` / `apply_pxr24_impl` | **No** |
+
+OpenEXR 2.5.4 has no `OpenEXRCore` tree. PXR24 lives only in
+`OpenEXR/IlmImf/ImfPxr24Compressor.cpp`.
+
+### 2. Legacy C++ PXR24 path is a different implementation
+
+`Pxr24Compressor::uncompress` uses zlib's `::uncompress()` and advances
+per-channel pointers with `n = numSamples(...)`, then bounds-checks against
+`tmpSize` (actual zlib output length). There is no `(uint64_t)(w * 3)`
+bounds expression that can wrap and bypass a check — the specific CVE root
+cause is not present.
+
+### 3. Published version criteria exclude 2.5.4
+
+CVE.org / NVD / GHSA-q3v8-hw4m-59w5 all list a minimum affected version of
+**3.2.0**. Bullseye's 2.5.4 is outside every published range.
+
+---
+
+## Recommended Disposition
+
+| Field | Value |
+|-------|-------|
+| CVE | CVE-2026-34380 |
+| Package | openexr / libopenexr25 / libopenexr-dev |
+| Installed version | 2.5.4-2+deb11u1 |
+| Affected range | 3.2.0–3.2.6 / 3.3.0–3.3.8 / 3.4.0–3.4.8 |
+| Assessment | **NOT AFFECTED** — below lower bound; OpenEXRCore and vulnerable expression absent |
+| Action required | None. Mark as false positive / not affected in scanner. |
+| Evidence | No `src/lib/OpenEXRCore/`. PXR24 is `ImfPxr24Compressor.cpp` with `tmpSize` guards; no `(uint64_t)(w * 3)`. |
+
+---
+
+## References
