Description: CVE-2026-34544 - Fix B44/B44A integer overflow in row pointer arithmetic
 Backport of upstream commit 35e7aa35 (OpenEXR v3.4.8) from the 3.x
 OpenEXRCore C library (src/lib/OpenEXRCore/internal_b44.c) to the 2.5.4
 C++ implementation (OpenEXR/IlmImf/ImfB44Compressor.cpp).
 .
 The B44/B44A encoder and decoder computed row pointer offsets as
 signed int * int multiplications: row0 = cd.start + y * cd.nx, with
 cd.nx (int) and y (int). When y * cd.nx exceeds INT_MAX (e.g.
 cd.nx = 268435456) the offset wraps, producing out-of-bounds reads or
 writes of HALF (uint16_t) samples while iterating 4x4 pixel blocks.
 .
 Fix: compute the row offset in uint64_t before pointer arithmetic, and
 widen the per-row stride additions (row1 = row0 + cd.nx, etc.) to
 uint64_t as well, mirroring the upstream C fix. Adds <cstdint> for
 uint64_t. The subsequent literal "+= 4" advances inside the inner loop
 are unchanged because they cannot overflow.
Origin: backport, https://github.com/AcademySoftwareFoundation/openexr/commit/35e7aa35e22c1975606be86e859f31cc1fc598ee
Bug: https://github.com/AcademySoftwareFoundation/openexr/security/advisories/GHSA-h762-rhv3-h25v
