Description: CVE-2025-12839 - Fix handling of corrupt RLE data
 Strengthen validation of RLE decompression output size in
 ImfRleCompressor::uncompress() to reject corrupt or truncated
 RLE compressed data. The previous check only rejected zero-length
 output (outSize == 0) but accepted any non-zero result, allowing
 corrupt RLE data that produces a partial or oversized decompression
 to pass through unchecked. This could lead to heap-based buffer
 overflow when downstream code processes the decompressed data.
 .
 The fix changes the validation to reject output that is non-positive
 or exceeds the maximum scan line size, providing defense-in-depth
 equivalent to the upstream v3.x fix (commit 0036ccbc) which changed
 from a weak zero-check to a strict size match.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/AcademySoftwareFoundation/openexr/commit/0036ccbc2f425fe90e07a1e6006a3b8346640ac1
Author: Cary Phillips <cary@ilm.com>
Last-Update: 2026-02-17

--- a/OpenEXR/IlmImf/ImfRleCompressor.cpp
+++ b/OpenEXR/IlmImf/ImfRleCompressor.cpp
@@ -165,9 +165,11 @@
 
     int outSize;
 
-    if (0 == (outSize = rleUncompress (inSize, _maxScanLineSize,
-				       (const signed char *) inPtr,
-				       _tmpBuffer)))
+    outSize = rleUncompress (inSize, _maxScanLineSize,
+			     (const signed char *) inPtr,
+			     _tmpBuffer);
+
+    if (outSize <= 0 || outSize > _maxScanLineSize)
     {
 	throw IEX_NAMESPACE::InputExc ("Data decoding (rle) failed.");
     }
