+## Why `CVE-2026-34379` Does Not Apply to Debian Bullseye `openexr` (2.5.4)
+
+## Overview: What Is OpenEXR?
+
+OpenEXR is a high dynamic-range (HDR) image file format developed by Industrial Light & Magic and maintained by the Academy Software Foundation. Debian Bullseye ships the `openexr` source package built from the **2.5.x** line (specifically **2.5.4-2+deb11u1**), which predates the modern C-core rewrite entirely.
+
+---
+
+## Why Scanners May Still Flag This CVE
+
+Security scanners (Trivy, Grype, etc.) may report **CVE-2026-34379** against OpenEXR because:
+
+* They match on **package name** (`openexr` / `libopenexr-*`) without applying **upstream version ranges** from the CVE record
+* They assume **any** OpenEXR build contains the same **C** DWA decoder layout as **3.2+**
+* **CVE.org** publishes explicit **affected version ranges**; tools that ignore them over-report
+
+Shipping an unnecessary backport of the upstream **C** fix can:
+
+* Fail to apply (the targeted file does not exist in 2.5.x trees at all)
+* Add audit noise and wasted build time
+* Obscure the fact that **this release is outside the vulnerable range**
+
+---
+
+## ⚠️ CVE Breakdown
+
+### CVE-2026-34379 – Misaligned memory access in `LossyDctDecoder_execute` (HALF→FLOAT)
+
+* **Component:** OpenEXR **C** core DWA decoder (`src/lib/OpenEXRCore/internal_dwa_decoder.h` in fixed branches)
+* **Issue:** Unsafe HALF-to-FLOAT expansion via casts that assume alignment; can misbehave on strict-alignment architectures and under aggressive optimizations
+* **Impact:** Potential crash or integrity issues when decoding crafted DWA content on affected versions
+* **Upstream fix:** [AcademySoftwareFoundation/openexr@fc58df6247d9dbc31995e57c7d65632792c24c5c](https://github.com/AcademySoftwareFoundation/openexr/commit/fc58df6247d9dbc31995e57c7d65632792c24c5c)
+
+---
+
+## Affected versions (per CVE.org)
+
+The CVE record lists affected product versions as (summary):
+
+* **OpenEXR** affected at **≥ 3.2.0, < 3.2.7**
+* **OpenEXR** affected at **≥ 3.3.0, < 3.3.9**
+* **OpenEXR** affected at **≥ 3.4.0, < 3.4.9**
+
+**Debian Bullseye `openexr` is 2.5.4**, which is **two major versions below 3.2.0** and therefore **outside all published affected ranges**. The vulnerability lives in code that did not yet exist when 2.5.x was released.
+
+---
+
+### Vulnerable versions (this hook target)
+
+| Distro | Release  | Package | Source version      | Status           |
+| ------ | -------- | ------- | ------------------- | ---------------- |
+| Debian | Bullseye | openexr | 2.5.4-2+deb11u1     | **Not affected** |
+
+---
+
+### Why the upstream patch file does not apply here
+
+* ✅ **2.5.x predates the C-core rewrite entirely.** OpenEXR 2.5 uses the legacy **IlmBase / OpenEXR / IlmImf** C++ layout — there is **no `OpenEXRCore` C library** in the source tree at all
+* ✅ **2.5.x does not ship** `src/lib/OpenEXRCore/internal_dwa_decoder.h`; that file (and the surrounding `OpenEXRCore` directory) was introduced as part of the OpenEXR **3.x** C-core rewrite
+* ✅ The legacy `OpenEXR/IlmImf/ImfDwaCompressor.cpp` HALF→FLOAT path in 2.5.4 uses `Xdr::read`/`Xdr::write` on `char*` buffers with `memcpy` into an aligned `std::vector<unsigned short>` — the **misalignment-UB pattern targeted by the upstream fix is structurally absent**
+* ✅ **CVE.org version criteria** already exclude **2.5.4** from affected bounds (minimum affected is 3.2.0)
+
+**Recommendation:**
+Treat **CVE-2026-34379** as **not applicable** for Debian Bullseye **openexr 2.5.4-2+deb11u1**. Prefer **documenting exclusion using CVE.org ranges** over forcing a code patch. For **3.2+ / 3.3+ / 3.4+** within the affected intervals, use the **real upstream fix** (or distro security update), not this documentation-only hook.
+
+---
+
+## Summary
+
+* CVE-2026-34379 applies to **OpenEXR ≥ 3.2.0** (per published ranges), not to **2.5.4**
+* Bullseye's **2.5.4-2+deb11u1** is **two major versions below** the minimum affected version
+* The targeted file `src/lib/OpenEXRCore/internal_dwa_decoder.h` and the entire `OpenEXRCore` C library do not exist in the 2.5.x source tree
+* No `internal_dwa_decoder.h` backport is required, possible, or appropriate for this package version
+* Scanner hits should be **reclassified as not affected** when the installed upstream version is **< 3.2.0**
+
+**Best practice:**
+Record the **CVE.org affected ranges** in compliance evidence and **exclude** this CVE from actionable remediation for **2.5.x** Bullseye images.
+
+---
+
+## References
+
+* [CVE.org – CVE-2026-34379](https://www.cve.org/CVERecord?id=CVE-2026-34379)
+* [Upstream fix commit fc58df6247d9dbc31995e57c7d65632792c24c5c](https://github.com/AcademySoftwareFoundation/openexr/commit/fc58df6247d9dbc31995e57c7d65632792c24c5c)
+* [OpenEXR (Academy Software Foundation)](https://github.com/AcademySoftwareFoundation/openexr)
+* [Debian Package: openexr (Bullseye)](https://packages.debian.org/bullseye/openexr)
